page.title: 04Housing in Eastchurch
page.content: In Eastchurch we found more {semi-detached houses}than any other types, 42, compared to 33 detached and 38 terraced. There is a school house which belongs to the school. Numbers 113 - 123 High Street are Airey Houses which are semi-detached and built of pre-fabricated concrete blocks. These houses were built just after World War II. Numbers 104 - 120 High Street were also built at this time and were {council houses}but are now privately owned. In the old terraced{housing}along Church road the people's{families}have lived there a long time. The newly built estate along Bramley Way is occupied by people whose families haven't lived in the area very long.
